{
    "title": "canonical cover",
    "html": "<div class=\"markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert dark\"><h3 data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"58\"><strong data-start=\"4\" data-end=\"56\">Closure of a Set of Functional Dependencies (F⁺)</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"59\" data-end=\"257\">The <strong data-start=\"63\" data-end=\"74\">closure</strong> of a set of functional dependencies (FDs), <strong data-start=\"118\" data-end=\"124\">F⁺</strong>, is the <strong data-start=\"133\" data-end=\"172\">set of all FDs that can be inferred</strong> from <strong data-start=\"178\" data-end=\"183\">F</strong> using <strong data-start=\"190\" data-end=\"212\">Armstrong’s Axioms</strong> (reflexivity, augmentation, transitivity).</p>\n<hr data-start=\"259\" data-end=\"262\">\n<h3 data-start=\"264\" data-end=\"303\"><strong data-start=\"268\" data-end=\"303\">Example: Finding Closure of FDs</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"304\" data-end=\"348\">Given <strong data-start=\"310\" data-end=\"334\">F = { A → B, B → C }</strong>, find <strong data-start=\"341\" data-end=\"347\">F⁺</strong>.</p>\n<h4 data-start=\"350\" data-end=\"387\"><strong data-start=\"355\" data-end=\"387\">Step 1: Start with Given FDs</strong></h4>\n<ul data-start=\"388\" data-end=\"431\">\n<li data-start=\"388\" data-end=\"409\"><strong data-start=\"390\" data-end=\"399\">A → B</strong> (Given)</li>\n<li data-start=\"410\" data-end=\"431\"><strong data-start=\"412\" data-end=\"421\">B → C</strong> (Given)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4 data-start=\"433\" data-end=\"474\"><strong data-start=\"438\" data-end=\"474\">Step 2: Apply Armstrong’s Axioms</strong></h4>\n<ul data-start=\"475\" data-end=\"542\">\n<li data-start=\"475\" data-end=\"542\">Using <strong data-start=\"483\" data-end=\"499\">transitivity</strong>:<br data-start=\"500\" data-end=\"503\">\n<strong data-start=\"505\" data-end=\"514\">A → B</strong> and <strong data-start=\"519\" data-end=\"528\">B → C</strong> ⟹ <strong data-start=\"531\" data-end=\"540\">A → C</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<h4 data-start=\"544\" data-end=\"582\"><strong data-start=\"549\" data-end=\"582\">Step 3: List All Inferred FDs</strong></h4>\n<span class=\"katex-display\" style=\"\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><msup><mi>F</mi><mo lspace=\"0em\" rspace=\"0em\">+</mo></msup><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>B</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>C</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F⁺ = \\{ A → B, B → C, A → C \\}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.8213em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height: 0.8213em;\"><span style=\"top: -3.113em; margin-right: 0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height: 2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">+</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span></span></span></span></span>\n<hr data-start=\"621\" data-end=\"624\">\n<h3 data-start=\"626\" data-end=\"644\"><strong data-start=\"630\" data-end=\"644\">Conclusion</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"645\" data-end=\"755\" data-is-last-node=\"\" data-is-only-node=\"\">The <strong data-start=\"649\" data-end=\"660\">closure</strong> <strong data-start=\"661\" data-end=\"667\">F⁺</strong> is the complete set of <strong data-start=\"691\" data-end=\"707\">all possible</strong> FDs that can be derived from a given set <strong data-start=\"749\" data-end=\"754\">F</strong>.</p></div><div class=\"markdown prose w-full break-words dark:prose-invert dark\"><h3 data-start=\"0\" data-end=\"39\"><strong data-start=\"4\" data-end=\"39\">Canonical Cover (Minimal Cover)</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"40\" data-end=\"204\">A <strong data-start=\"42\" data-end=\"61\">canonical cover</strong> (or <strong data-start=\"66\" data-end=\"83\">minimal cover</strong>) of a set of Functional Dependencies (FDs) is a simplified version of the original FDs that is <strong data-start=\"179\" data-end=\"193\">equivalent</strong> but has:</p>\n<ol data-start=\"205\" data-end=\"452\">\n<li data-start=\"205\" data-end=\"274\"><strong data-start=\"208\" data-end=\"228\">No redundant FDs</strong> (removing an FD should change the closure).</li>\n<li data-start=\"275\" data-end=\"370\"><strong data-start=\"278\" data-end=\"306\">No extraneous attributes</strong> (removing an attribute from an FD should change the closure).</li>\n<li data-start=\"371\" data-end=\"452\"><strong data-start=\"374\" data-end=\"414\">Only one attribute on the right side</strong> (i.e., decomposed into atomic FDs).</li>\n</ol>\n<hr data-start=\"454\" data-end=\"457\">\n<h3 data-start=\"459\" data-end=\"496\"><strong data-start=\"463\" data-end=\"496\">Steps to Find Canonical Cover</strong></h3>\n<ol data-start=\"497\" data-end=\"713\">\n<li data-start=\"497\" data-end=\"567\"><strong data-start=\"500\" data-end=\"565\">Break FDs so that each FD has only one attribute on the right</strong></li>\n<li data-start=\"568\" data-end=\"637\"><strong data-start=\"571\" data-end=\"603\">Remove extraneous attributes</strong> from the left side if possible.</li>\n<li data-start=\"638\" data-end=\"713\"><strong data-start=\"641\" data-end=\"665\">Remove redundant FDs</strong> if their removal does not change the closure.</li>\n</ol>\n<hr data-start=\"715\" data-end=\"718\">\n<h3 data-start=\"720\" data-end=\"735\"><strong data-start=\"724\" data-end=\"735\">Example</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"736\" data-end=\"748\">Given FDs:</p>\n<span class=\"katex-display\" style=\"\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>B</mi><mi>C</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>C</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F = \\{ A → BC, B → C, A → C \\}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.07153em;\">BC</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span></span></span></span></span>\n<h4 data-start=\"787\" data-end=\"857\"><strong data-start=\"792\" data-end=\"857\">Step 1: Break into atomic FDs (single attribute on the right)</strong></h4>\n<span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mi>F</mi><mo>=</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>B</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>C</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">F = \\{ A → B, A → C, B → C \\}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.13889em;\">F</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span></span></span></span></span>\n<h4 data-start=\"895\" data-end=\"932\"><strong data-start=\"900\" data-end=\"932\">Step 2: Remove redundant FDs</strong></h4>\n<ul data-start=\"933\" data-end=\"1060\">\n<li data-start=\"933\" data-end=\"1036\"><strong data-start=\"935\" data-end=\"944\">A → C</strong> is redundant because we can derive <strong data-start=\"980\" data-end=\"989\">A → C</strong> from <strong data-start=\"995\" data-end=\"1004\">A → B</strong> and <strong data-start=\"1009\" data-end=\"1018\">B → C</strong> (transitivity).</li>\n<li data-start=\"1037\" data-end=\"1060\">So, remove <strong data-start=\"1050\" data-end=\"1059\">A → C</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-start=\"1062\" data-end=\"1090\">Final <strong data-start=\"1068\" data-end=\"1087\">canonical cover</strong>:</p>\n<span class=\"katex-display\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" display=\"block\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">{</mo><mi>A</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>B</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>B</mi><mo>→</mo><mi>C</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">}</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\{ A → B, B → C \\}</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">{</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">A</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 0.8778em; vertical-align: -0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.05017em;\">B</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">→</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right: 0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height: 1em; vertical-align: -0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right: 0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"mclose\">}</span></span></span></span></span>\n<hr data-start=\"1117\" data-end=\"1120\">\n<h3 data-start=\"1122\" data-end=\"1140\"><strong data-start=\"1126\" data-end=\"1140\">Conclusion</strong></h3>\n<p data-start=\"1141\" data-end=\"1283\" data-is-only-node=\"\" data-is-last-node=\"\">The <strong data-start=\"1145\" data-end=\"1164\">canonical cover</strong> is a minimal equivalent set of FDs.<br data-start=\"1200\" data-end=\"1203\">\nFor <strong data-start=\"1207\" data-end=\"1239\">F = { A → BC, B → C, A → C }</strong>, the <strong data-start=\"1245\" data-end=\"1282\">minimal cover is { A → B, B → C }</strong>.</p></div>"
}